[0.005, "o", "\u001b[32m╭─\u001b[0m\u001b[32m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[32m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;32mAssistant\u001b[0m\u001b[32m \u001b[0m\u001b[32m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[32m─╮\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  To install Firefox using zypper, you need to follow these steps:                                                                   \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0mOpen the ZYPPER terminal by typing \"zypper\" in your command line and pr"]
[0.000, "o", "essing Enter. This will open a console where you can     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mrun commands.                                                                                                                   \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0mType \u001b[1;36;40msudo\u001b[0m at the beginning of each command that requires sudo privileges (e.g., \u001b[1;36;40mzyprex\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mzyprefs\u001b[0m). You may need to enter your    \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mpassword when prompted for this step.                                                                                           \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0mExecute the following command:                                                                                                  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[48;2;39;40;34m                                                  "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                               \u001b[0m  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[48;2;39;40;34m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34mzypper\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34maddrepo\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34mhttps://dl.opensuse.org/repositories/home:/user/firefox\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34m/var/cache/yum/x86_64-linux-gnu\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;39;40;34m                         \u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;39;40;34m \u001b[0m  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[48;2;39;40;34m                                                                                                                                 \u001b[0m  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  Replace \"username\" with your user name and \"/path/to/directory\" with the path where you want to"]
[0.000, "o", " store Firefox packages (e.g.,      \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[1;36;40m/usr\u001b[0m or \u001b[1;36;40m~\u001b[0m). This command will add a repository for the home:/user/firefox package collection, which contains all available         \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  versions of Mozilla Firefox on that system. 4. Execute this command:                                                               \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[48;2;39;40;34m                                                                                                                                 \u001b[0m  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[48;2;39;40;34m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34mzypper\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34minstall\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;248;248;242;48;2;39;40;34mfirefox\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;39;40;34m                                "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                         \u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;39;40;34m \u001b[0m  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[48;2;39;40;34m                                                                                                                                 \u001b[0m  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  Replace \"username\" with your user name and \"/path/to/directory\" again (e.g., \u001b[1;36;40m/usr\u001b[0m or \u001b[1;36;40m~\u001b[0m) where you want to store the downloaded     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  packages, followed by a period character (\u001b[1;36;40m..\u001b[0m). This will download Firefox from the repository specified in step 3 above into that  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  directory. 5. Verify if firefox has been installed successfully: Try running \"firefox\" command at your terminal and check for any  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  errors or warnings (e.g., `Error: No br"]
