[0.001, "o", "\u001b[32m╭─\u001b[0m\u001b[32m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[32m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;32mAssistant\u001b[0m\u001b[32m \u001b[0m\u001b[32m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[32m─╮\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  Yet Another Startup Tool is an open source system administration tool for Linux systems. YaST provides a graphical user interface  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  (GUI) to configure and manage various aspects of the operating system, including hardware devices such as hard disks or network    \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  interfaces, software packages like applications and services, and boot configuratio"]
[0.000, "o", "n settings.                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  YaST's main features include:                                                                                                      \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0mA web-based GUI for managing system configurations;                                                                             \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0mSupport for multiple operating systems (Linux distributions);                                                                   \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0mAbility to create customized templates with user-friendly interfaces for various device types or services; and             "]
[0.000, "o", "     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 4 \u001b[0mIntegration with other open source tools, such as Samba file sharing, OpenSSH remote access, or LVM logical volume management,  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mamong others.                                                                                                                   \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m╭─\u001b[0m\u001b[2m─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[2m \u001b[0m\u001b[2mSources\u001b[0m\u001b[2m \u001b[0m\u001b[2m─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[2m─╮\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2m  • Expert Partitioner | Reference | openSUSE Leap 15.6 (52%)\u001b[0m                                                                       \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2;34m    https://doc.opensuse.org/documentation/leap/reference/html/book-reference/cha-expert-partitioner.html\u001b[0m                           \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2m  • YaST in text mode | Reference | openSUSE Leap 15.6 (52%)\u001b[0m                                                                        \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2;34m    https://doc.opensuse.org/documentation/leap/reference/"]
[0.000, "o", "html/book-reference/cha-yast-text.html\u001b[0m                                    \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\u001b[0m\r\n"]
