[0.001, "o", "\u001b[32m╭─\u001b[0m\u001b[32m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[32m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;32mAssistant\u001b[0m\u001b[32m \u001b[0m\u001b[32m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[32m─╮\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  Sure, I'd be happy to provide a brief overview of what makes openSUSE special. Here are some key features and benefits:            \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0mOpen source software: openSUSE is based on the popular Linux distributi"]
[0.000, "o", "on SUSE, which means that it uses free and open-source   \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mtechnologies such as kernel development, user management tools like YaST, and package management system APT (Another Package    \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mTool). This makes openSUSE a safe choice for developers who want to experiment with new software without worrying about         \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mlicensing issues.                                                                                                               \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0mCommunity support: The openSUSE project is heavily supported by the community of users and contributors around the world. You   \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mcan find an extensive set of resources on the official website, including online documentation, tutorials, videos, forums, and  \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0ma dedicated bug tracker where you can report bugs or request new features.             "]
[0.000, "o", "                                         \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0mFlexibility: openSUSE is designed to be flexible enough to support different hardware configurations (from small desktop        \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mcomputers up to large enterprise servers) as well as various operating systems such as Linux, BSD, Solaris, and Windows. This   \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mflexibility allows you to customize the system configuration according to your needs without requiring extensive knowledge of   \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mcomplex software stacks or programming languages.                                                                               \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 4 \u001b[0mSecurity: openSUSE is designed with security in mind from day one by incorporating strong encryption algorithms into its        \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mkernel development process as well as providing comprehensive network and application firewalling solut"]
[0.000, "o", "ions, among others.      \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mThis makes it a safe choice for users who value their privacy and confidentiality online.                                       \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[36m 5 \u001b[0mCommunity-driven: openSUSE is built on the back of a vibrant community that contributes to its success by                       \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[32m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m╭─\u001b[0m\u001b[2m─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[2m \u001b[0m\u001b[2mSources\u001b[0m\u001b[2m \u001b[0m\u001b[2m─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[2m─╮\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2m  • About this guide | Reference | openSUSE Leap 15.6 (62%)\u001b[0m                                                                         \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2;34m    https://doc.opensuse.org/documentation/leap/reference/html/book-reference/preface-reference.html\u001b[0m                                \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2m  • About this guide | Reference | openSUSE Leap 15.6 (58%)\u001b[0m                                                                         \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2;34m    https://doc.opensuse.org/documentation/leap/reference/"]
[0.000, "o", "html/book-reference/preface-reference.html\u001b[0m                                \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\u001b[0m\r\n"]
